title: Story of Temple Drake (1933) William Faulkner Miriam Hopkins
description:
Based on William Faulkner's Sanctuary, this tells the story of a fast-living rich girl who gets in over her head when she stumbles into a den of thuggish bootleggers. It somewhat reminds me of The Grissom Gang (1970) - you can see the resemblances between Temple Drake and Barbara Blandish - surely Robert Aldrich took a close look at this. It is surprising that such a story made it to the screen in the 1930s.

There is said to be a restored version making the rounds, this is definitely not it. This is a small file, you can judge whether yu think it worth chasing after a better one.
